<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-23T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-23T08:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6211/71: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-23T16:00:00+03:00">August 23,
                                    1939—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 23—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>461. Ribbentrop arrived promptly at 1:00 by air and was met at the
                            airport on behalf of the Soviet Government by Potemkin, the Commander of
                            the Moscow garrison, and other Soviet officials. He was to see Molotov
                            at 3 o’clock this afternoon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>